               <p>Creswell. I myself was accused by a letter with having received Neal's money due to 
               <persName id="t17690628-65-person652">
                  Margaret 
                  Campbell 
               <interp inst="t17690628-65-person652" type="surname" value="Campbell"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-65-person652" type="given" value="Margaret"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-65-person652" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , for wages due on board the Ludlow Castle.</p>
               <p>Q. Is that money paid, or still due?</p>
               <p>Creswell. It is still due for what I know. I have a letter here to assure me that the money is not paid. The books are now at Portsmouth. I never did receive a farthing of that money.</p>
               <p>Q. Was there wages due to 
               <persName id="t17690628-65-person653">
                  James 
                  Neal 
               <interp inst="t17690628-65-person653" type="surname" value="Neal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-65-person653" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17690628-65-person653" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             of the Ludlow Castle?</p>
               <p>Creswell. There was.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you know any thing of the prisoner?</p>
               <p>Creswell. I never saw him till to-day, to my knowledge.</p>
               <p>
            
